          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Gas transit discussion</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-dec-24-2.jpg" alt="Gas transit discussion" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Slovak Prime Minister Robert Fico <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-dec-2024-4-held-talks" target="_blank">held talks</a> with Russian President Vladimir Putin in Moscow, marking a rare visit by an EU leader since Russia's 2022 invasion of Ukraine. The talks were mainly centered around gas transit and the Ukraine war following Ukraine's announcement that it would not renew a vital gas deal with Slovakia.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Fico, known for his pro-Russia stance, emphasized Slovakia's reliance on Russian gas and nuclear energy while criticizing EU sanctions on Russia's nuclear program. He claimed Putin remains open to delivering gas to Europe and discussed normalizing Slovak-Russian relations. The opposition and many EU leaders were not pleased with this meeting. The only two face-to-face meetings were with Hungary's PM <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-dec-2024-5-viktor-orban" target="_blank">Viktor Orbán</a> and Austrian Chancellor <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-dec-2024-6-karl-nehammer" target="_blank">Karl Nehammer</a>.​</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
