          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇷🇸 Serbia:</strong>    
          Serbians <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-dec-2024-9-gathered" target="_blank">gathered</a> in Belgrade on Sunday for a massive protest against the government, sparked by the <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-dec-2024-10-novi-sad-train-station" target="_blank">Novi Sad train station</a> roof collapse that killed 15 people seven weeks ago. The student-led movement, supported by farmers, actors, and educators, began with 15 minutes of silence to honor the victims. Protesters blame corruption and negligence for the tragedy. President Aleksandar Vucic, who previously dismissed the protests, expressed openness to dialogue. Authorities have shortened the school term and promised subsidies for youth, but public frustration remains high over perceived corruption and incompetence.</p>
        </mj-text>
