          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇸🇾 Syria:</strong>   
          Ahmed al-Sharaa, Syria’s interim leader, <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-dec-2024-11-announced" target="_blank">announced</a> that all armed factions, including those in Kurdish-led areas, will be dissolved and integrated into a national army under state control. He stated that this standing was made by Turkish Foreign Minister Hakan Fidan al-Sharaa, who emphasized unifying military authority to prevent sectarian discord and external exploitation. Fidan urged lifting international sanctions on Syria to aid recovery and resettle displaced people. He also called on U.S. President-elect Donald Trump to end support for the Kurdish-led Syrian Democratic Forces, which Turkey links to the PKK. This policy marks a shift towards centralized governance after the rebel offensive that toppled Bashar al-Assad.</p>
        </mj-text>
